<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcb7acab2-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s31707"><num value="31707">§ 31707.</num><heading> Limitations on statutory construction</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Sections 31704 and 31705 of this title do not limit the amount of money a State may charge for registration of a commercial motor vehicle or the amount of any fuel use tax a State may impose.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idcb7acab3-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/272/s1/e">Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(e)</ref>, <date date="1994-07-05">July 5, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/1033">108 Stat. 1033</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
